{
  "text": "A straightforward approach to addressing the aforementioned adverse factors may be achieved by performing nonsupervised image segmentation. However, in most image segmentation methods, the number of image modalities must be known a priori [CITATION_1] . Therefore, for a field image as shown in Figure 2 where the number of different texture regions is arbitrary, segmentation approach is not practical.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "53924538"
